                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Φιλοκ_"><abbr>Φιλοκ</abbr></name></persName>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><abbr>Philok</abbr>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><abbr>Philok</abbr>.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><abbr>Philok</abbr>.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>An abbreviated personal name as in <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr113000</ref>, <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr111800</ref> and <ref type="inscription" source="#IGCyr2">IGCyr113600</ref>, probably the dedicant's name.</p>
                <p>This abbreviated form might be completed into names such as <foreign xml:lang="grc">Φιλόκαλος</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Φιλοκλῆς</foreign>,
                    <foreign xml:lang="grc">Φιλοκράτης</foreign> or <foreign xml:lang="grc">Φιλόκωμος</foreign>, all already attested in Cyrenaica.</p>
            </div></body>
